original: Kronberg, Gustaf, komminister, Norrköping, f. 26/5/76 i Al, Kopparb. 1., av P. A. Kronberg o. Anna Persson. G. 03 m. Frida Berggrensson. Barn: Nils f. 04. — Utex. fr. Metodistkyrkans teol. isemin. i Upps. 03, prästex. i Härnösand 16. Metodist-pastor i Heby 02, Surahammar 03-08, Lindesberg 09-10, Malmö 10-12, Kristinehamn 12-13, Trollhättan 13-15, pastorsadj. i Torps församl. i Medelpad 15-16, v. pastor i Selånger 16-20, kommin. i Arnäs församl. i Anger-manl. 20-21, dito i Hedvigs församl. i Norr köp. sed. 21.
translated: Kronberg, Gustaf, vicar, Norrköping, b. 26/5/1876 in Al, Kopparb. 1., son of P. A. Kronberg and Anna Persson. Married in 1903 to Frida Berggrensson. Children: Nils b. 1904. Graduated from the Methodist Church's theological seminary in Uppsala in 1903, ordained as a priest in Härnösand in 1916. Methodist pastor in Heby 1902, Surahammar 1903-1908, Lindesberg 1909-1910, Malmö 1910-1912, Kristinehamn 1912-1913, Trollhättan 1913-1915, assistant pastor in Torp parish in Medelpad 1915-1916, assistant pastor in Selånger 1916-1920, vicar in Arnäs parish in Angermanland 1920-1921, and the same in Hedvigs parish in Norrköping since 1921.
